definition: Dwight D. Eisenhower (1890-1969), US army general and politician, Supreme Allied Commander in Europe during World War II, US President 1953-1961
Chinese mugwort or wormwood/moxa/to stop or cut short/phonetic "ai" or "i"/abbr. for 艾滋病[ai4 zi1 bing4], AIDS

sentences.english: Now you're not spying for Eisenhower anymore, you're working for me.
sentences.chinese: 現在你不用再爲艾森豪威爾當坐探了，你爲我幹活吧。

sentences.english: Eisenhower realized that he could not fail with highways.
sentences.chinese: 艾森豪威爾意識到他押寶高速公路不會輸。

sentences.english: I thought his prose style was about the level of General Eisenhower's.
sentences.chinese: 我原以爲他的文字水平並不比艾森豪威爾將軍高明哩。

sentences.english: Eisenhower secretly ordered the Pentagon to build ICBMs with "maximum urgency."
sentences.chinese: 艾森豪威爾祕密命令五角大樓集中全力研發洲際導彈。

sentences.english: F: Will, President Eisenhower was known as Ike.
sentences.chinese: 嗯，艾森豪威爾總統也被呢稱爲艾克。

sentences.english: One week later, the German army surrendered to Eisenhower and the Allies.
sentences.chinese: 一週後，德軍正式向艾森豪威爾和盟軍投降。

sentences.english: Dwight Eisenhower came from a large family in Abilene, Kansas.
sentences.chinese: 艾森豪威爾來自一個大家族，在堪薩斯州阿比林。

sentences.english: Eisenhowers' favorite comment seemed to be "do whatever it takes".
sentences.chinese: 艾森豪威爾最喜歡的評語似乎是“不惜一切代價”。

sentences.english: Eisenhower left the White House and retired to his farm in Gettysburg.
sentences.chinese: 艾森豪威爾離開白宮，退隱到他在葛底斯堡的農場。

sentences.english: Eisenhower, vaccine, England's got a new queen.
sentences.chinese: 艾森豪威爾，預防針，英國新女王。

sentences.english: F: Well, President Eisenhower was known as Ike.
sentences.chinese: 嗯，艾森豪威爾總統也被呢稱爲艾克。

definition: General Douglas MacArthur (1880-1964), US commander in Pacific during WW2, sacked in 1951 by President Truman for exceeding orders during the Korean war
Jawaharlal Nehru (1889-1964), Indian politician, first prime minister 1947-1964
Netanyahu (name)/Benjamin Netanyahu (1949-), Israeli Likud politician, prime minister 1996-1999 and from 2009
